<div layout="row" layout-align="space-around center">
  <div class="blurb-box single md-whiteframe-5dp" layout="column">
    <header class="md-accent-bg md-hue-1">
      <div class="title">Module Objectives</div>
    </header>

    <div class="content">
      <ul class="md-headline objectives">
        <li>
	  Be able to identify the relation between between a poll's <strong>population</strong> size and its <strong>sample</strong>
	</li>
        <li>
	  Develop a sense for how <strong>sample bias</strong>
	  affects a poll's accuracy
	</li>
	<li>
	  Become familiar with a famous story of biased polling methods
	</li>
	<li>
	  Be able to mark whether a poll is of good <strong>quality</strong> rather than
	  just large in the sense of <strong>quantity</strong>
	</li>
	<li>
	  Be able to explain how it is that an <strong>unbiased</strong> small
	  poll is likely
	  <em>more accurate</em> than a <strong>biased</strong> large poll
	</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
